<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Here's my theory, 90% sure it's right:<P>1. Thru a combination of sieves, ToT, & the mob casting, bring mob mana to zero (or very close.)<BR>Note: this requires a fairly long fight.<P>2. Mobs regen a lot of mana per tic, but typically not enough for a CH.  <BR>Therefore chain sieving should keep them from ever starting a CH.<P>3. Most high-end mobs regen enough between sieves to Gate (and some enough to CH).  <BR>Therefore you can't stop them from trying a Gate.  <BR>Instead, you have to wait until they begin to cast, then land a sieve in the 4-second window of Gate's casting time.<BR>Upon resolution of the Gate spell, the server checks if the mob has the required mana. <BR>If you've drained it dry just before, the spell fizzles.<BR>Note: ToT works too if the mob isn't immune.<P>Sound correct?<P>m3<BR>mt
</FONT>
<HR size="1" color="#dedfdf">
