<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Seiving during a cast wont do any good.. if it starts casting the spell its as good as cast unless you get VERY lucky and have everyone including rogues pushing from the same side to interrupt it.<P>IMO the best thing to do is if you have 2 or more enchanters and are really worried about gate/CH, stagger casts slightly, so that the seives land at even intervals and prevent it from regaining too much mana. Also be sure and try to land Torment of Argli because then it will have a lot less of a chance to regen enough mana to cast.<P>Also, don't forget, if there's a time you ABSOLUTELY NEED IT SEIVED *NOW*, bring a Phinny rod, 7 charges of instant cast seive will bring even the fastest dying gater to its knees.
</FONT>
