<HR size="1" color="#dedfdf">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
<BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">quote:</font><HR>Originally posted by meeke:<BR><STRONG>2. Mobs regen a lot of mana per tic, but typically not enough for a CH.  <BR>Therefore chain sieving should keep them from ever starting a CH.</STRONG><HR></BLOCKQUOTE><P>Mobs don't regen a lot of mana per tick.  In fact, they regen very little.  They do, however, pay a much reduced mana cost on all spells.  So basically, instead of, say, regenning 300 per tick and having CH cost 400... they regen 30 per tick and it costs them 40.<P>Actual mob regen values are lower than 30 really.  Torment of Argli keeps most any mob dry (haven't found one yet that it doesn't, once you get it dry) and does this while helping to move it towards OOM, so it's safe to assume that mob regen is less than the per tick mana reduction for Torment of Argli.  Certain mobs may be an exception to this, but none that I've run across yet.<P>Anyway, that distinction only really matters when you are altering the mob's mana regen rate, but it is something to keep in mind.
</FONT>
<HR size="1" color="#dedfdf">
