<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Jaya pointed this out to me ...<P>If you see:<P>"Creature begins to cast the gate spell."<P>that means it has decided it wants to gate.  If it actually has enough mana to cast gate, the next line will be:<P>"Creature begins to cast a spell."<P>So, if you see the first line, but not the second, that is proof that your sieving task is going well and the creature does not have enough mana to gate away.<P>And, in agreement with the other posters here, Torment of Argli plus a couple of sieves usually does the trick.<P>--------------------<P><A HREF="http://www.geocities.com/xymarra" TARGET=_blank>Xymarra Elen-gariel</A><BR><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=18486" TARGET=_blank>Elven Enchanter</A> of the <A HREF="http://arbiters.econfcall.com/" TARGET=_blank>Arbiters</A> on <A HREF="http://vnboards.ign.com/board.asp?brd=5011" TARGET=_blank>E'Ci</A><BR><A HREF="http://www.geocities.com/xymarra/Quest/Quest.html" TARGET=_blank>Enchanter epic quest walkthrough</A>, <A HREF="http://www.geocities.com/xymarra/Strategy/EnchanterStrategy.html" TARGET=_blank>Enchanter strategy guide</A>, <A HREF="http://www.geocities.com/xymarra/Spells/SpellLists.html" TARGET=_blank>Printable spell lists</A>
