<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
<BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">quote:</font><HR>Mobs don't regen a lot of mana per tick. In fact, they regen very little. They do, however, pay a much reduced mana cost on all spells. So basically, instead of, say, regenning 300 per tick and having CH cost 400... they regen 30 per tick and it costs them 40.<HR></BLOCKQUOTE>Asterix, I'd LOVE to know where you got this information from. Frankly, unless you have a source who's got access to Verant's code I'd have to say this is just another example of someone taking a wild guess and stating it as truth.<P>There are very few things that are actually known about how mobs cast. One of them is that the mobs in ToV and several other high-end zones have much smaller mana pools than seen on std exp mobs like the frogs in Sebilis. You can test this by using ToT at the start of a fight and seeing how much mana is returned. CH costs these mobs a lot more than gate, and argli on its own is often enough to stop them casting a CH. To prevent them gating you need to argli and then toss in a few sieves when it's getting low on health.
