<BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">quote:</font><HR>It's common game knowledge. A mob that is actively engaged in combat regens less mana than one out of combat. When out of combat, they regen mana at an incredible rate.<HR></BLOCKQUOTE>Ok, I'm going to have to burst your bubble here. Not only is 'common game knowledge' nothing more than a collection of hearsay and rumour, it's also completely and utterly wrong in this case.<P>Try doing some real tests. In my experience with using DC on shaman mobs (which will cast heal spells on themselves when below 50% health), they will stop healing themselves when low after many fights. If you rest for a minute, they start healing themselves again. Gasp! Could it be that the mob has actually had to spend some time regenning mana?? Duh. Cast C2 on the pet and it regens mana faster. I'm not sure how /pet sit down affects this, as sitting the pet usually causes it to wander, so I don't use it.<P>This 'mobs regen mana at an incredible rate' myth needs to get exploded.
