No, actually ToT has nothing to do with the amount of mana mobs have; thats why PCs could ToT other PC non casters before for mana, before they altered coding; ToTs mana return is mostly level based, which is why your kor frog gives you nearly a bubble, but your krup gives half that, and your myconid barely moves it at all, unless the resist roll goes really low.<P>As for casting, I have heard you can interrupt spells by sieving it dry after it starts casting. The way its supposed to work is-<P>Mob wants to CH<BR>It checks mana pool- enough for CH, begins casting<BR>ToTs hit it and drain pool<BR>At end of spell, checks again, not enough, mob loses.<P>Now on the gate issue, they will try w/o enough mana; it just wont cast. Quite an annoying text line when your in a big fight and nothing can get away.<P>--------------------<P>Dexanth Dragonborne<BR>60th Phantasmist of Fennin Ro
