<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
I have never "interupted" a gate or CH from a seive, the most I've seen is prevented them. <P>Try this in a duel sometime, sieve a cleric down to nothing, have them spamclick a CH button. When they start to cast, seive them once, they will have less mana than needed to complete the cast.<P>The cast will still go through if it's not interupted. Granted this is not an NPC but it does pay a bit of testiment. If you have the mana to cast the spell in the first place, you WILL cast the spell, and the second mana check simply brings whatever the total is to zero if it goes over, as those mana calculations are handled after-the-fact (simmilar to why you can't cast X spell until you have a bub of mana, but after casting still have 1/4th blue... the specialization/reduction bonus clicks AFTER the spell is finished).<P>Food for thought anyway.
