Ive never had a sieve that landed after casting begun stop a cast and I tested it hundreds of times on players in PVP about 2 years ago, something could have been changed since then though.<P>Theft of thought returns mana based on the level of the NPC target, for level 50 and less it drains and gives the entire 400, for each level the NPC is higher than that, expect 10% less drain and 10% less return.<P>I did this like 600 times in east wastes and it worked like this every time:<BR>1. Tishania coldain missionary<BR>2. It either casts a DD or runs toward me<BR>3. Mez/fear/DD it then mez it again and theft.<BR>4. Repeat mez/fear/dd until 2 minute mark but dont kill it.<BR>5. Theft it again when it recycles.<BR>6. Here I would kill it, BUT for fun or if it resisted a DD it would break the mez and begin chain casting 40 HP heals on itself.<P>This leads me to believe that:<BR>1. My first theft drained ALL or ALMOST ALL of its mana.  I never had one cast after breaking fear once I thefted it early in the fight, they always just tried to melee me.<BR>2. The second theft drained them totally to OOM.<BR>3. The mob never regenned enough mana since it was aggrod to cast anything except low HP heals.<BR>4. If blurred and let sit for a few seconds it would regen mana VERY quickly and CH itself.<P>Tsunamii Starshine<BR>55 Enchantress Rallos Zek<P>--------------------<P>Tsunamii Starshine
