<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
I obviously know nothing about the high-end enchanter game since I don't have one, but perhaps ToT works like normal damage spells in that the mob has a chance to partially resist the ToT, and have only a little drained.<P>If this is the case, then the mob would have a chance to resist your ToT spell based on its level compared to yours and some check based upon its magic resistance (if that is the resistance type ToT checks against). It might be instructive to run some rests with/without tashing and with different level enchanters trying to ToT the same mob, and compare results.<P>Just a thought about stealing thoughts. =)
