<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
I'm going to throw in my two bits:<P>A *LONG* time ago there was a news post on casters realm reguarding monsters and their regen rates.  One of the developers confirmed that monsters regen mana MUCH more slowly during combat, than they do out of combat.<P>As to the cost of spells that a monster pays, who knows.  I do know that mana sieve saps 214-370 mana per cast from a monster.  (According to the castersrealm info).  And I know that it takes upwards of 4-5 casts on a myconoid adept before it won't try to CH itself anymore.<P>During most fights an adept (I'm using adepts as an arbitrary example) seem to have enough mana for 2-3 nukes, 1 or 2 dispels, and 3 CHs if you don't sieve them down at all.<P>Now if it takes me 4 casts of mana sieve (seems like it takes more, but lets just pick 4 as an example) to sieve an adept down to where it won't CH, and lets also assume that mana sieve is doing 300 mana per shot.  (Just to make the math easier).<P>That means I'm sieving out aprox 1200 mana from an adept just to try and prevent it from CHing.<P>That, to me, kind of points in the direction of monsters having larger mana pools, and paying full cost for spells.<P>But I could be and probably am wrong, but thats my intuitive guess based on just tons and tons of observation.<P>- Pahbi
</FONT>
